If you&rsquo;re usually using print(...) in Swift to print debug info to the output console, it might be difficult to fight muscle memory and use os_log(...) instead.
Luckily, you can easily create a simple replacement for print() if you want to route some of that sweet, sweet debug info to the app logs and from there see them straight in dataTile!
Additionally, you might have some print statements sprinkled here and there and want to now capture them with dataTile&hellip;
